                <h1>Understanding Pearl Harbor: A Defining Moment in U.S. History</h1>
                <p>Pearl Harbor, a U.S. naval base in Hawaii, was the site of a surprise military attack by Japan on December 7, 1941. This event led to significant loss of life and prompted the United States to enter World War II. Pearl Harbor symbolizes a pivotal moment in American history, highlighting the impacts of war and foreign relations.</p>
